# React Hook Imports

Import hooks (and other hook-like APIs) as named imports from `"react"`. Call them directly, not via the `React` namespace.

## ❌ Bad

```tsx
import React from "react";

React.useEffect(() => {}, []);
React.useState(0);
React.useCallback(fn, []);
```

## ✅ Good

```tsx
import { useCallback, useEffect, useState } from "react";

useEffect(() => {}, []);
useState(0);
useCallback(fn, []);
```

## Rule

1. Add each hook you use to the import list from `"react"` (e.g. `useEffect`, `useState`, `useRef`, `useMemo`, `useCallback`, `useContext`, `useReducer`, `useLayoutEffect`, `useId`, …).
2. Use the imported identifier in the file body.
3. A default `import React from "react"` is fine when needed for JSX or `React.*` types — but hooks must still be named imports, not `React.use*` calls.
